      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i was looking at my mortgage statement from wells fargo and im a bit confused. i have a 30 year fixed at 6.5%. if i'm about 5 years in, it feels like i'm barely touching the principal. can u explain how the math works for the principal vs interest part of the payment? like how does it change over the life of the loan?",
